268 Geometric Inequalities
Postulate 7.7
EXAMPLE I
Proof
Subtraction of inequalities is restricted to a single case:
If equal quantities are subtracted from unequal quantities, then the differ-
ences are unequal in the same order.
However, when unequal quantities are subtracted from unequal quantities,
the results may or may not be unequal and the order of the inequality may or
may not be the same.
For example:
• 5 > 2 and 4 > 1, but it is not true that 5 - 4 > 2-1 since 1 = 1.
• 12 > 10 and 7 > 1, but it is not true that 12 - 7> 10 - 1 since 5 < 9.
• 12 10 and 2 > 1, and it is true that 12 2 10 - 1 since 10 > 9.
